    "comments": [
      "Information of tracklisting from Hal C F Astell's website.",
      "This show should have included an Iron Maiden concert but technical problems prevented that. It was ultimately broadcast the following week.",
      "After the first set, Tommy mentions that Patience is being released 'this coming Monday'. That was, in fact, 19 Jun 1989 in the UK (it entered the Top 40 w/e 1st July, broadcast on 25 June), dating this show correctly to 16 Jun 1989. This fits with Tommy's opening comment of 'rock music for a summer night.'",
      "Quite a lot of skipping records in this show.",
      "After the Johnny Diesel track, Tommy mentions that he'll be standing in for Alan Freeman on the Saturday Rock Show the next day."
    ]
  },
